pspm_ecg_editor: Epoch file with epochs of artefacts (to be ignored)

pspm_dcm_inv: contains the data to adjust the RF to
minimum dispersion (standard deviation) for flexible responses (default 0.1 s)
pspm_dcm: Minimum dispersion (standard deviation) for flexible responses. Default: 0.1s.
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): Minimum dispersion (standard deviation) for flexible responses. Default: 0.1s.

pspm_emg_pp: [numeric/string] Channel to be preprocessed. Can be a channel ID or a channel name. Default is 'emg' (i.e. first EMG channel)
pspm_gaze_pp: [numeric/string, optional] Channel ID to be preprocessed.

pspm_emg_pp: ['add'/'replace'] Defines whether the new channel should be added or the previous outputs of this function should be replaced. (Default: 'rplace')

pspm_gaze_pp: [numeric/string, optional] Channel ID to be combined.

pspm_find_valid_fixations: Choose channels in which the data should be set to NaN during invalid fixations

pspm_dcm_inv: update CRF priors to observed SCRF, or use pre-estimated priors (default)
pspm_dcm: Update CRF priors to observed SCRF, or use pre-estimated priors (default)
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): Update CRF priors to observed SCRF, or use pre-estimated priors (default)

pspm_dcm_inv: no of trials to invert at the same time (default: 2)
pspm_dcm: No of trials to invert at the same time. Default: 2.
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): No of trials to invert at the same time. Default: 2.

pspm_data_editor: file must be a struct with an 'epoch' field

pspm_dcm_inv: contains the data to estimate RF from

pspm_dcm: Cell array of names for individual events
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): Cell array of names for individual events

pspm_exp: exclude parameters from conditions with too many NaN values. This option can only be used for GLM files when exclude_missing was set during model setup. Otherwise this argument is ignored (Default: 0).
pspm_glm: a struct marks trials during which NaN percentage exceeds a cut-off value

pspm_find_sounds: [integer] Checks for correct number of detected sounds

pspm_find_valid_fixations: Define on which eye the operations should be performed.

pspm_ecg_editor: To what factor should potentially wrong hb events

pspm_find_valid_fixations: A nx2 vector containing x and y of the fixation point

pspm_dcm_inv: fixed events to adjust amplitude priors
flexible events to adjust amplitude priors
only estimate RF, do not do trial-wise DCM
pspm_dcm: Only estimate RF, do not do trial-wise DCM
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): Only estimate RF, do not do trial-wise DCM

pspm_ecg_editor: Channel id of the existing hb channel

pspm_dcm: Estimate the response function from the data. Default: 0.
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): Estimate the response function from the data. Default: 0.

pspm_extract_segments: Length of the segments in the 'timeunits'. If given the same length is taken for segments for glm structure. If not given lengths are take from the timing data. This argument is optional. If 'timeunit' equals 'markers' then 'length' is expected to be in seconds. For dcm structures the option length will be ignored and length will be set from timing data.

pspm_emg_pp: [integer] Frequency of mains noise to remove with notch filter (default: 50Hz).

pspm_extract_segments: Mandatory if timeunit is 'markers'. For the function to find the appropriate timing of the specified marker ids. Must have the same format as data_fn. If timeunit is 'markers' and raw data are given then this parameter should be an cell array of numeric array of marker data.

pspm_glm: double, default as the last marker channel number
pspm_trim: first marker channel is used by default

pspm_dcm_inv: data to adjust the response amplitude priors to
data points to be disregarded by inversion
pspm_find_valid_fixations: If missing is enabled (=1), an extra channel will be written containing information about the validated data.
pspm_split_sessions: Optional name of an epoch file

pspm_extract_segments: This option defines whether the user wants to output the NaN ratios of the trials for each condition. If so,  we values can be printed on the screen (on MATLAB command window) or written to a created file. The field can be set to 'screen', 'File Output'or 'none'. 'none' is the default value.

pspm_find_valid_fixations: Define new filename to store data to it, default is ''

pspm_extract_segments: If 1, z-scores the entire data time series (default: 0).

pspm_dcm: Don't save dcm structure (e.g. used by pspm_get_rf)
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): Don't save dcm structure (e.g. used by pspm_get_rf)

pspm_convert_ecg2hb_amri: a 'heartbeat' channel to the given PsPM file

pspm_data_editor: a file the changed data is saved to

pspm_extract_segments: Define filename to store segments. If is equal to '', no file will be written. Default is 0.

pspm_dcm: whether to overwrite. Default: determined by pspm_overwrite.
pspm_down: whether to overwrite. Default: determined by pspm_overwrite.
pspm_extract_segments: Define if already existing files should be overwritten. Default ist 0.
pspm_find_valid_fixations: Define whether existing files should be overwritten or not. Default is 0.
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): whether to overwrite. Default: determined by pspm_overwrite.
pspm_segment_mean: file specified in options.newfile will be overwritten

pspm_extract_segments: If 1 mean values (solid) and standard error of the mean (dashed) will be ploted. Default is 0.
pspm_segment_mean: Display plot of the mean of each condition

pspm_find_valid_fixations: Define whether to plot the gaze coordinates for visual inspection of the validation process.

pspm_find_sounds: [integer] spline interpolates the sound by the factor specified.

pspm_find_valid_fixations: Resolution with which the fixation point is defined

pspm_dcm_inv: use pre-specified RF, provided in file, or as 4-element vector in log parameter space
pspm_dcm: Call an external file to provide response function (for use when this is previously estimated by pspm_get_rf)
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): Call an external file to provide response function (for use when this is previously estimated by pspm_get_rf)

pspm_find_sounds: [vector of 2 floats] Region of interest for discovering sounds

pspm_dcm_inv: scl-change-free window after last event (default 5 s)
pspm_dcm: scl-change-free window after last event. Default: 5s.
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): scl-change-free window after last event. Default: 5s.

pspm_dcm_inv: scl-change-free window before first event (default 2 s)
pspm_dcm: scl-change-free window before first event. Default: 2s.
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): scl-change-free window before first event. Default: 2s.

pspm_ecg_editor: Defines whether to navigate between potentially wrong hb events only (semi = 1), or between all hb events (semi = 0 => manual mode)

pspm_dcm_inv: maximum frequency of SF in ITIs (default 0.5/s)
pspm_dcm: maximum frequency of SF in ITIs. Default: 0.5/s.
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): maximum frequency of SF in ITIs. Default: 0.5/s.

pspm_dcm_inv: sf-free window after last event (default 5 s)
pspm_dcm: sf-free window after last event. Default: 5s.
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): sf-free window after last event. Default: 5s.

pspm_dcm_inv: sf-free window before first event (default 2 s)
pspm_dcm: sf-free window before first event. Default: 2s.
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): sf-free window before first event. Default: 2s.

pspm_find_sounds: [integer] number of the channel holding the sound

pspm_exp: 'param': export all parameter estimates (default) | 'cond': GLM - contrasts formulated in terms of conditions, automatically detects number of basis functions and uses only the first one (i.e. without derivatives) other models - contrasts based on unique trial names | 'recon': export all conditions in a GLM, reconstructs estimated response from all basis functions and export the peak of the estimated response
'screen' (default), or a name of an output text file

pspm_extract_segments: 'seconds' (default), 'samples' or 'markers'. In 'auto' mode the value will be ignored and taken from the glm model file or the dcm model file. In the case of raw data the timeunit should be seconds.

pspm_find_sounds: [integer] number of the channel holding the triggers

pspm_dcm: Cell array of names for individual trials, is used for contrast manager only (e.g. condition descriptions)
pspm_get_rf (inherited from pspm_dcm): Cell array of names for individual trials, is used for contrast manager only (e.g. condition descriptions)

pspm_gaze_pp: [bool] 1 or 0. 1 if use valid samples produced by pspm_pupil_pp, 0 if not to use. default as 0.

pspm_write_channel: default value is 0, contains channel id of added / replaced / deleted

pspm_scr_pp: create a .mat file saving the epochs
